; Regression test for issue #617: bal --anon anonymizes *before* it generates the report (BZ#617)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/617
;
; The --anon flag should anonymize account names and amounts in the REPORT OUTPUT,
; but the bug causes it to anonymize before report generation. The account name
; hash varies per posting (seeded randomly), so the same account hashes differently
; across postings, breaking balance accumulation. Each posting becomes its own
; "account" instead of being rolled up by account name.
;
; Using --format to show only amounts (skipping non-deterministic hashed names)
; and --sort T for deterministic ordering.
;
; Current (broken) behavior: 4 separate entries (one per posting, no accumulation)
;   A-200.00, A-100.00, A100.00, A200.00
; Correct behavior after fix: 2 entries with accumulated totals
;   A-300.00, A300.00

2024/01/01 Groceries
    Expenses:Food    $100.00
    Assets:Checking    $-100.00

2024/01/15 More Groceries
    Expenses:Food    $200.00
    Assets:Checking    $-200.00

test bal --anon --sort T --format "%(display_total)\n"
A-200.00
A-100.00
A100.00
A200.00
0
end test
